name: Evergreen State Fairgrounds Covid-19 Vaccine Site
info:
**************THIS IS MODERNA CLINIC******************
Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form). 

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves. 

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) vaccine is also available for people 18 years and older. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante.  Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 12-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 1750 112th Avenue Northeast, STE C-102, Bellevue WA, 98004
info: ***We currently are providing the 1st and 2nd doses of MODERNA.*** Please sign up for an appointment time. When you arrive to the clinic, please continue to wear your face covering, practice physical distancing and wash your hands frequently to help reduce transmission. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Due to the limited supplies of vaccines provided to us each week, we are unable to take walk-ins, so please make an appointment. ***Directions to the Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine:*** Our clinic is located in the Hidden Valley Office Complex. 1) When you arrive at the complex, take either driveway all the way to the back of the building. 2) We are located on the prominent corner at the very back of the building and we have our own private entrance. Look for the parking lot with the number "2" in a big steel frame. Do NOT go into the main building for we have a private entrance accessible directly from the parking lot. Look for our sign with our logo in the window and a door with the number "C-102" on it, visible from the parking lot. *If you would like to find out more information about our clinic, please visit our website at www.hawkerhealth.com

name: Skagit County Public Health- Fairgrounds
address: Skagit County Fairgrounds 1410 Virginia St., Mount Vernon WA, 98273
info:
Pfizer Dose 1 & 2 Vaccine Clinic 
•	North Entrance to Skagit County Fairgrounds 1410 Virginia Street, Mount Vernon WA
•	Child watching provided
•	Vaccination process will take approximately 1 hour.  Wheel chairs and accessible parking available for people with mobility challenges.
•	All forms available in English and Spanish.  Spanish language interpretation provided.  
•	Dose 2 appointments scheduled 3 weeks following 

We are unable to vaccinate people who have received another vaccine of any type within 14 days OR those that have severe allergic reactions to vaccines or injectable medications.


Clínica de vacunas de primer y Segundo dosis Pfizer
•	Entrada norte al recinto ferial del condado de Skagit 1410 Virginia Street, Mount Vernon WA
•	Vigilancia de niños proveída
•	El proceso de vacunación durará aproximadamente 1 hora. Sillas de ruedas y estacionamiento accesible para personas con problemas de movilidad.
•	Todos los formularios están disponibles en inglés y español. Interpretación en español será proveída.

No podemos vacunar a personas que hayan recibido otra vacuna de cualquier tipo durante los ultimos 14 días O personas que tengan reacciones alérgicas graves a vacunas o medicamentos inyectables.

name: Ocean Shores Convention Center
address: 120 West Chance a La Mer Northwest, Ocean Shores WA, 98569
vaccines: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine
info: This clinic is held within the Ocean Shores Convention Center. This clinic is for the 2nd dose of Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine and the one-dose Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) COVID-19 vaccine. This clinic is only held for adults 18 years and older. Anyone receiving their second dose must have had the PFIZER VACCINE in order to get the second dose of the Pfizer vaccine. You CANNOT mix brands of the COVID-19 vaccine. The supply of the Janssen vaccine is limited. Please bring a face covering to your appointment that covers the mouth and the nose and if you are getting your second dose, please bring your vaccine card. If you cannot locate your vaccine card, proof of first vaccination and type of vaccine must be provided. All persons receiving the vaccine are required to stay under observation 15-30 minutes post-vaccination.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic

info: ***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** ***Please notify us of a cancelation ASAP, we have patients on waiting list, and would prefer not to waste vaccines*** You must provide insurance (photo ID if you do not have insurance) by one of the 2 methods below before you check-in for vaccine. Upload options 1. Prepmod at time of sign up 2. bring your insurance card to your visit. We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine. Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine. Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available. Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.
